  "body": "As an Besu operator, \r\nI want have a new NAT Method based on DNS entry\r\nso that I can configure Besu with a p2p-network based on that method. \r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\nWhen a private network is configured with NAT method (DNS) where announcement IP is the same that the private IP HOST, the Besu operator could rely on DNS to resolve the listen and announcement of besu node.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:** [What you expect to happen]\r\n1. Start besu with --nat-method=DNS and p2p-host=besu.yourdomain.tld defined\r\n2. Besu starts with the PeerDiscoveryAgent configured in the IP associated to the domain besu.yourdomain.tld\r\n\r\n**Frequency:** [What percentage of the time does it occur?]\r\nRequired when Docker NAT method is not able to determine the IP\r\n\r\n### Versions (Add all that apply)\r\nAll\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n",
